      "@type": "Project",
      "schema:legalName": "eOceans",
      "schema:name": "eOceans",
      "schema:url": "https://www.eoceans.app",
      "schema:description": "eOceans has two pillars: 1) a cloud-based Platform-as-a-Service (PaaS) that automates ocean data processing and 2) co-generated research that uses the eOceans PaaS to track different dimensions of the ocean on an as-needed basis. \r\n1. The eOceans PaaS (eOceans.app) helps teams collect and analyze ocean data in near real-time at any spatial and temporal scale. The platform has two main parts: i) mobile app for at-sea scientists, citizen scientists, and all other explorers to track their activity (geolocated and timestamped effort) and log observations of animals and human dimensions (e.g., pollution, fishing activities) on the go and ii) analytical and dissemination tools that analyze the data streaming from the mobile app, and other sources (e.g., OBIS, API) and share results with stakeholders and rightsholders in near rea-time. The analytics available include sumaries, advanced biological, social, and anthropogenic spatiotemporal trends and their interactions, and two proprietary trackers — MPA Health Tracker and Smart Fishery Tracker, which include a suite of analytics to scalably track marine protected areas and fisheries (e.g., stock assessments) in near real-time. \r\n2. eOceans Research (eOceans.org) uses the eOceans PaaS to conduct monitoring and research on various species groups and issues, including eShark, eManta, eSeaTurtle, ePollution, eFishKill, eWhale, eWhaleStrandings, The Great Fiji Shark Count, etc. Our research is varied, but typically involves co-generated science where local experts are integral to the project for data collection, interpretation, and results application. \r\nWith the eOceans app, data contributors own their data and decide what projects they contribute to. Therefore, eOceans research data stay within the eOceans platform (not downloaded or exported) so that contributors feel comfortable that their data are not be used elsewhere and they always can see what their contributions support. \r\nThe eOceans platform shares data to third parties only as requested by the contributor.",
